<BR>@&nbsp;
<A HREF="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/From_the_Founding_of_the_City/Book_27#6"><FONT CLASS="ref">~</FONT>Liv_27.6'8.</A>
<TR><TH VALIGN=TOP> <A NAME=3>3</A>
<TD> <FONT CLASS="green">GRE</FONT> <FONT CLASS="ref"><<</FONT> <B> <A CLASS="help" HREF="../names/z/zenon.html#2">Zenon</A> of <A CLASS="help" HREF="../names/c/citium.html#1">Citium</A> sets himself up as an independent teacher of philosophy.</B>
<BR><FONT CLASS="orange"> *</FONT> <A HREF="../old/diogenes7a.html#2">Read Diogenes' account</A>
<BR>@&nbsp;
<A HREF="../old/diogenes7a.html#2">DiogLaert_7'2,</A><FONT CLASS="orange">*&nbsp;</FONT>
<A HREF="../old/diogenes7a.html#4">'4;</A>
<FONT CLASS="ref">{</FONT> Zenon attended philosophy lectures for twenty years after his arrival in Athens, before setting himself up as a teacher.<FONT CLASS="ref">}</FONT>
<TR><TH VALIGN=TOP> <A NAME=3a>3a</A>
<TD> <FONT CLASS="ref"><<</FONT> <I>Document:</I><B> <A HREF="../translate/epicurus.html#U127">Epicur:Fr_127,</A> </B> a letter from <A CLASS="help" HREF="../names/e/epicurus.html#1">Epicurus</A> to <A CLASS="help" HREF="../names/t/themista.html#1">Themista.</A>
<TR><TH VALIGN=TOP> <A NAME=4>4</A>
<TD> <FONT CLASS="green">ROM</FONT> <B> <A CLASS="help" HREF="../names/m/megellus.html#1">L.Postumius</A> is recalled from his province, and subsequently brought to trial on a charge of misuse of his troops.</B>
<BR><FONT CLASS="orange"> *</FONT> <A HREF="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus/17*.html#4">Read Dionysius' account</A>
